column5: No real time for fishing, not enough snow for snowmobiling. Plus, you sorta gotta be around family through the holidays so I spent time in the shop along with visiting and such.    we have...jewelry boxes. From a plan I found in a magazine while Christmas shopping. If you're gonna do the tool setup, may as well make it worth while.
Birdseye maple and Cherry.      still glueing up drawers for the third one, but i has to get some finish on the 2 that were done.  Still need to add the green velvet linning to the drawers.
beautiful! Love the birds eye maple!, wish I could find it at a decent price for flooring!  love the design too!  G.
the mill where I get it has their office floor all done with birdseye and tiger maple..its pretty impressive
Excellent Dara Always nice spending time in the shop when you don't have any other choices!!! Leechman
WOW!  Thats stunning Dara.  Beautiful craftsmanship....love the cherry wood.
Beautiful, I was hoping they were some kind of up scale tackle box/ lure holders! Look great either way even if you want to use them for jewelry.
Kinda has a Dr Seuss appeal to them...and im starting to feel like a rerun Excellent job Dara ...these for sale too?

Never thought of that george. I always told my wife that i thought some of them fancy salmon lures would make good earings. They would prolly look good in that box too....maybe a pair of hammered gold sweedish pimples with red blades on em.  yes twocoda...for sale...I need snowmobile gas money
